  <section id="S4" refnum="4">
    <title>Test of number-swapping</title>
    <para id="S4.p1">
      <p>This is a repeat of the first section but with numbers in theorem heads
swapped to the left.</p>
    </para>
    <para id="S4.p2">
      <p>Ahlfors' Lemma gives the principal criterion for obtaining lower bounds
on the Kobayashi metric.</p>
    </para>
    <theorem id="ThmAhlforsx2">
      <title>
        <text font="bold">Ahlfors' Lemma.</text>
      </title>
      <p>
        <text font="italic">Let <Math mode="inline" tex="ds^{2}=h(z)|dz|^{2}" text="d * s ^ 2 = h * z * | * d * z * | ^ 2"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="eq" role="RELOP" font="upright">=</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" possibleFunction="yes">h</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" open="(" close=")">z</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="upright">|</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">z</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="upright">|</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math> be a Hermitian pseudo-metric on
<Math mode="inline" tex="\mathbf{D}_{r}" text="D _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="bold upright">D</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>, <Math mode="inline" tex="h\in C^{2}(\mathbf{D}_{r})" text="h in C ^ 2 * D _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="in" role="RELOP" font="upright">∈</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">h</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" possibleFunction="yes">C</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp><XMApp open="(" close=")"><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="bold upright">D</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math>, with <Math mode="inline" tex="\omega" text="omega"><XMath><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok></XMath></Math> the associated
<Math mode="inline" tex="(1,1)" text="OpenInterval@(1, 1)"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok name="OpenInterval" role="FENCED" argclose=")" argopen="(" separators=","/><XMTok meaning="1" role="NUMBER" font="upright">1</XMTok><XMTok meaning="1" role="NUMBER" font="upright">1</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>-form. If <Math mode="inline" tex="\mathop{\mathrm{Ric}}\nolimits\omega\geq\omega" text="Ric * omega greater-eq omega"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="greater-eq" name="geq" role="RELOP" font="upright">≥</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="FUNCTION" scriptpos="post" font="upright">Ric</XMTok><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok></XMApp><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math> on <Math mode="inline" tex="\mathbf{D}_{r}" text="D _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="bold upright">D</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>,
then <Math mode="inline" tex="\omega\leq\omega _{r}" text="omega less-eq omega _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="less-eq" name="leq" role="RELOP" font="upright">≤</XMTok><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math> on all of <Math mode="inline" tex="\mathbf{D}_{r}" text="D _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="bold upright">D</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math> (or equivalently,
<Math mode="inline" tex="ds^{2}\leq ds_{r}^{2}" text="d * s ^ 2 less-eq d * (s _ r) ^ 2"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="less-eq" name="leq" role="RELOP" font="upright">≤</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math>).
</text>
      </p>
    </theorem>
    <theorem id="S4.Thmthmsw1" refnum="4.1">
      <title>
        <text font="bold">4.1 Lemma (negatively curved families).</text>
      </title>
      <p>
        <text font="italic">Let <Math mode="inline" tex="\{ ds_{1}^{2},\dots,ds_{k}^{2}\}" text="Set@(d * (s _ 1) ^ 2, dots, d * (s _ k) ^ 2)"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok name="Set" role="FENCED" argclose="}" argopen="{" separators=",,"/><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok meaning="1" role="NUMBER" font="upright">1</XMTok></XMApp><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp><XMTok name="dots" role="ID" font="upright">…</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">k</XMTok></XMApp><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math> be a negatively curved family of metrics
on <Math mode="inline" tex="\mathbf{D}_{r}" text="D _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="bold upright">D</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>, with associated forms <Math mode="inline" tex="\omega^{1}" text="omega ^ 1"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMTok meaning="1" role="NUMBER" font="upright">1</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>, …, <Math mode="inline" tex="\omega^{k}" text="omega ^ k"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">k</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math>.
Then <Math mode="inline" tex="\omega^{i}\leq\omega _{r}" text="omega ^ i less-eq omega _ r"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="less-eq" name="leq" role="RELOP" font="upright">≤</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">i</XMTok></XMApp><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok name="omega" role="UNKNOWN">ω</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">r</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math> for all <Math mode="inline" tex="i" text="i"><XMath><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">i</XMTok></XMath></Math>.
</text>
      </p>
    </theorem>
    <para id="S4.p3">
      <p>Then our main theorem:</p>
    </para>
    <theorem id="S4.Thmthmsw2" refnum="4.2">
      <title>
        <text font="bold">4.2 Theorem.</text>
      </title>
      <p>
        <text font="italic">Let <Math mode="inline" tex="d_{{\max}}" text="d _ max"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMTok meaning="max" role="LIMITOP" scriptpos="post" font="upright">max</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math> and <Math mode="inline" tex="d_{{\min}}" text="d _ min"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok role="SUBSCRIPTOP" scriptpos="post3"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMTok meaning="min" role="LIMITOP" scriptpos="post" font="upright">min</XMTok></XMApp></XMath></Math> be the maximum, resp. minimum distance
between any two adjacent vertices of a quadrilateral <Math mode="inline" tex="Q" text="Q"><XMath><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">Q</XMTok></XMath></Math>. Let <Math mode="inline" tex="\sigma" text="sigma"><XMath><XMTok name="sigma" role="UNKNOWN">σ</XMTok></XMath></Math>
be the diagonal pigspan of a pig <Math mode="inline" tex="P" text="P"><XMath><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">P</XMTok></XMath></Math> with four legs.
Then <Math mode="inline" tex="P" text="P"><XMath><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">P</XMTok></XMath></Math> is capable of standing on the corners of <Math mode="inline" tex="Q" text="Q"><XMath><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">Q</XMTok></XMath></Math> iff
</text>
      </p>
      <equation id="E2" refnum="2" label="sdqsw">
        <Math mode="display" tex="\sigma\geq\sqrt{d_{{\max}}^{2}+d_{{\min}}^{2}}." text="sigma greater-eq sqrt@((d _ max) ^ 2 + (d _ min) ^ 2)">
